<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Faction system won't solve this problem</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:08 a.m. 17/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Faction system won't solve this problem<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=974" TARGET=_self>Faction system won't solve this problem</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Better ask Brad to leave everyone blue until they reach 5th

<BR>&gt; level. Faction hits won't help, in fact they will only serve to
<BR>&gt; legitimize newbie slaying even further. Now high level groups of
<BR>&gt; humans can, for example, journey to Nektulos and slaughter
<BR>&gt; newbies in the name of role playing. The idea that they might
<BR>&gt; even gain faction standing for it makes it worse still!
<P>There are a couple of reasons why this won't happen.
<P>1. Supose you are a mid-level dark elf necromancer and you hear about how a bunch of human players are killing newbies right outside your front door. Are you just going to ignore it? I think not. The problem will solve itself. Newbies will "aquire" bodyguards if they are going into dangerous areas. "Dangerous areas" might well be defined as "anyplace without guards".
<P>2. There is still a +4/-4 level limit on killing. So in order to kill newbies, you would have to be fifth or less level. Which is not eaxctly MY definition of "high level". Your mileage may vary. Of course, a fifth level anything would be hell on wheels in a newbie zone.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
